### useTransition

`useTransition` lets you mark state updates as non-urgent transitions. Urgent updates (like input changes) remain responsive while transitions (like filtering lists) happen in the background.

---

### Syntax

```jsx
import { useTransition } from 'react';

const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();
```

### Basic Usage

```jsx
function Search() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

  const handleChange = (e) => {
    // Urgent: update input display
    setQuery(e.target.value);

    // Non-urgent: filter results
    startTransition(() => {
      setFilteredItems(filterItems(items, e.target.value));
    });
  };

  return (
    <>
      <input value={query} onChange={handleChange} />
      {isPending && <Spinner />}
      <List items={filteredItems} />
    </>
  );
}
```

### When to Use

| Situation | Use Transition? |
|-----------|---------------|
| Input changes | Urgent (no) |
| Filtering long lists | Non-urgent (yes) |
| Navigation tabs | Non-urgent (yes) |
| Animations | Non-urgent (yes) |
| API call results | Non-urgent (yes) |

### useTransition vs useDeferredValue

| Feature | useTransition | useDeferredValue |
|---------|---------------|------------------|
| Control | Wraps state update | Wraps the value |
| Use case | You control the update | Value comes from props |
| Pending flag | `isPending` | Manual comparison |

> **Key Point:** Use startTransition for state updates that can be interrupted. The isPending flag lets you show loading indicators without blocking the UI. Do not use transitions for urgent updates like form validation.

codeExample:
import { useState, useTransition } from 'react';

function TabView() {
  const [tab, setTab] = useState('home');
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

  const switchTab = (newTab) => {
    startTransition(() => {
      setTab(newTab);
    });
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={() => switchTab('home')}>Home</button>
      <button onClick={() => switchTab('settings')}>Settings</button>
      {isPending && <p>Loading...</p>}
      <TabContent tab={tab} />
    </div>
  );
}
